  <bioghist id="74dacfcb78e34ffa3780113c400af481">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Richard M. Krasno's career in education has included positions in academia, philanthropy, and government. Krasno worked for several years at the Ford Foundation. In 1974, he joined the Foundation as a Program Advisor in the Latin America and the Caribbean, Brazil Program. He then became a Program Officer in the umbrella Latin America and the Caribbean Program before moving to the Middle East and Africa Program.</p><p>After leaving the Ford Foundation, Krasno served in the United States Department of Education as Deputy Assistant to the Secretary of Education. He then had executive positions at the Institute of International Education, the Monterey Institute of International Studies, and the William R. Kenan, Jr, Charitable Trust. He later became Lead Director for Ladenburg Thalmann Financial Services.</p><p>Krasno earned a Ph.D. from Stanford University and worked as an assistant professor at the University of Chicago prior to joining the Ford Foundation.</p>  </bioghist>
